title: Easy Slow Cooker Chicken and Dumplings

Ingredients.3: 1 salt and ground black pepper to taste

Ingredients.5: 1 (10.75 ounce) can  low-sodium chicken broth, divided

Ingredients.10: 1 (10.75 ounce) can  reduced-fat condensed cream of celery soup (such as Campbell's®)

Ingredients.11: 1 (10.75 ounce) can  reduced-fat condensed cream of chicken soup (such as Campbell's® Healthy Request)

Ingredients.13: 1 (10 ounce) package refrigerated biscuit dough, torn into pieces

Directions.1: Whisk water, poultry seasoning, salt, and black pepper together in a bowl; add chicken to the bowl and turn to coat.

Directions.2: Pour 1/2 of the chicken broth into a slow cooker; add chicken and poultry seasoning mixture. Layer onion, carrots, and celery, respectively, over chicken. Dot butter over vegetables; pour both condensed soups and remaining broth over vegetables, then sprinkle rosemary on top.

Directions.3: Cook on High for 3 1/2 to 4 1/2 hours. Remove chicken from slow cooker and shred with two forks; return chicken to slow cooker. Add biscuit dough pieces to the chicken mixture. Cook on High for 1 1/2 hours.
